

                What You Get            
By                     
                                    JULIE LASKY
                            
                JAN. 10, 2018
    

            CreditBob Fuller        
WHAT A gabled 1910 house with a double-decker front porch, three bedrooms and two and a half bathrooms
HOW MUCH $249,900
SIZE 1,760 square feet
PRICE PER SQUARE FOOT $142
SETTING This home is near the Ohio City neighborhood of Cleveland, about 15 minutes from downtown and not far from parks, bars, restaurants, gyms and rapid transit.
INDOORS A thorough renovation project that was completed last year modernized the interior while preserving some architectural details, like built-in seating and cabinetry. The main level has an open floor plan, with the living room — which has a bay window and brick fireplace with a gas insert and flanking bookshelves — flowing into a kitchen with steel appliances and granite counters. Opposite the kitchen, the dining area retains its original dark-wood bench and glass-paned cabinets. A salvaged door slides on wheels along a metal track at the entrance to the powder room. Engineered hardwood floors and recessed lighting are found throughout this level.
Upstairs, a master suite has access to the upper porch. The master bathroom has a pair of glass basin sinks. Two additional bedrooms and a bathroom are on this floor; one of the bedrooms opens onto a sun porch with a vaulted wood ceiling.
Advertisement
OUTDOOR SPACE A detached two-car garage reached by a paved driveway was recently added to the .09-acre property.
Advertisement
TAXES $2,383
CONTACT Joe Vaccaro, the Vaccaro Team, 216-650-8188; howardhanna.com
