INDOORS The home was extensively renovated between 2009 and 2012, and its original oak floors and trim have been restored. The living room has a wood-burning fireplace with a slate-tile surround and a bar built into a cabinet next to it. An adjacent sun porch is currently used as a home office. The oak-beamed dining room has built-in china cabinets and a set of French doors leading to a screened wraparound porch. The new kitchen has heated floors, a breakfast bar with storage and a recently added powder room. A second half bathroom is in the basement.
Upstairs, a sleeping porch off a bedroom was converted into a sitting room and bathroom to create a master suite. The sitting room has a gas fireplace. Two additional bedrooms on this floor share a bathroom with a combined tub and shower.
OUTDOOR SPACE The 50-by-140-foot lot includes a professionally landscaped backyard and a stained-concrete patio. A detached two-car garage has access from two sides and includes a raised area inside that could be used for potting plants.
TAXES $3,522
CONTACT Roy Nowers, Skogman Realty, 319-350-4042; skogman.com
 •
WHAT A cottage built in 1930, with two bedrooms and two bathrooms
HOW MUCH $221,500
SIZE 1,150 square feet
PRICE PER SQUARE FOOT $193
SETTING About 15 minutes northwest of downtown Little Rock, the home is in a neighborhood of small vintage houses that is becoming increasingly popular, especially with investors. Some nearby houses have been razed and are being replaced with large, expensive houses.
Advertisement
INDOORS The home was gutted and completely remodeled in the last year, with new wiring and plumbing. The floors were redone, the windows replaced and the kitchen and both bathrooms updated. The front porch gable was rebuilt in a period style.
The single-story house includes a living-and-dining area, a kitchen that leads to a sun porch, a master bedroom with an en-suite bathroom and a guest room with another en-suite bathroom. A wall of windows in the master bedroom overlooks the backyard.
OUTDOOR SPACE The pillared front porch is wide enough for a swing. The backyard is enclosed by a new wooden fence and trellis.
TAXES $2,301
CONTACT Carol Jenkins, Adkins, McNeill, Smith & Associates, 501-960-6040; littlerockishome.com
An earlier version of this article misidentified Ohio City. It is a neighborhood in Cleveland, not a suburb.
